column3: 1. Satisfaction: What is your feeling with respect to your overall experience with CNCF, where 5 is completely met expectations and 1 is did not meet expectations? *
column4: 2. Collaboration: Do you feel that CNCF reached out to collaborate and gather info about your project’s needs?
column5: 3. Were there explicit requests that you made of CNCF staff that you felt were ignored?
column6: 4. Efficiency: Did you feel that the CNCF team responded quickly to your requests? Where 5 is work was completed on time or ahead of schedule and 1 is delayed?
column7: 5. Were you happy with KubeCon + CloudNativeCon in Austin in Dec 2017?
column8: 6. How can CNCF help you and/or your project in the next 6 months?
column9: 7. Any other feedback that you wish to share, from what CNCF can do more or what we should do less?

column7: Didn’t attend but heard it wasn’t good overall
column9: I think the CNCF should help more with project websites so that they have a consistent look.  The projects can help with content. There are no standard templates that can be used that look good for modern infrastructure projects.

Sell more T-shirts / sweatshirts with our project logo.  Each one we see gives us all a morale boost!

More discussions about how to boost via marketing would also help.  We'd be happy to work more closely with the CNCF on this.

column9:
containerd and Notary are considered to be under the Moby Project umbrella (which is out of CNCF) but this relation ship does not seem documented in CNCF documents.
I'd expect CNCF to help clarifying this.
